# Object pool (ScenePool)

## Infrastructure

- Single pool service: `Game/ObjectPools` node, script `game/pool/scene_pool.gd` (`class_name ScenePool`).
- Helpers: `game/pool/pool_util.gd` — `PoolUtil.release_node(node)`.
- API: `acquire(scene: PackedScene, parent: Node)`, `release(node: Node)`. Buckets keyed by `PackedScene.resource_path`; no per-type pool classes.
- `acquire` order: `pool_reset` → reparent to caller parent → `_activate` → set `_pooled_active` → `pool_on_acquire()` last. Caller applies position/`setup()`/`initialize_spawn_health` after `acquire` returns.
- Prewarm: `_prewarm_scene` must `add_child` to `ObjectPools` before `_deactivate` so pooled scenes run `_ready()` once.
- Prewarm counts are `@export` on `ObjectPools` in `survivors_game.tscn`.

## Must (pooled node script)

- Implement `pool_reset()` and `pool_on_acquire()` for nodes that re-enter play.
- Do not use `_ready()` for per-spawn setup (runs once). Spawn state belongs in `pool_on_acquire` or caller setup (e.g. `Mob.initialize_spawn_health`).
- Remove gameplay groups in `pool_reset` (`mobs`, `exp_orbs`); re-add in `pool_on_acquire`.
- End lifetime with `PoolUtil.release_node(self)`, not `queue_free()`, when the node was acquired from the pool.

## Must (spawn callers)

- Mobs: `Game.spawn_mob()` → `ScenePool.acquire` → set `global_position` → `initialize_spawn_health`.
- Exp orbs: `mob.gd` `_die()` → `acquire(EXP_ORB_SCENE, parent)` → set position.
- Projectiles / orbit magic: `gun.gd` `_spawn_from_pool` → setup → `PoolUtil.release_node` on end.
- Area damage (연금 착지 등): `concoction.gd` → `ScenePool.acquire(AREA_DAMAGE_ZONE_SCENE)` → `setup_circle` → `PoolUtil.release_node` on zone lifetime end. Prewarm: `prewarm_area_damage_zones`.
- Melee pierce projectiles: `gun.gd` `_shoot_melee_projectile` → `MELEE_PROJECTILE_SCENE` → `PoolUtil.release_node` at range end. Prewarm: `prewarm_melee_projectiles`.
- Mob ranged: `mob.gd` telegraph → `acquire(MOB_ATTACK_MARK_SCENE)` parent=mob → timer → `release` mark → `acquire(MOB_PROJECTILE_SCENE)` parent=spawn layer → `PoolUtil.release_node` on projectile end. Prewarm: `prewarm_mob_attack_marks`, `prewarm_mob_projectiles` on `ObjectPools`.

## Not pooled (current)

- `magnet_pickup`, `health_pickup`: `mob.gd` `_die()` uses `instantiate` + `queue_free` on `collect()` (low drop rate). If pooled later, add `pool_reset`/`pool_on_acquire` and replace `queue_free` with `PoolUtil.release_node`.

## Must (mob pool)

- `pool_reset`: clear status, `collision_layer = 0`, `collision_mask = 0`.
- `pool_on_acquire`: restore `collision_layer = 2`, `collision_mask = 3`, `add_to_group("mobs")`.
- `_die()` must still call `Game.register_kill()` before `PoolUtil.release_node(self)`.

## When adding a new mob scene

- Update `MobSpawnSelector` and `scene_pool.gd` mob prewarm list in `_ready()` in the same change.

## When adding a new pooled projectile scene

- Add `pool_reset` / `pool_on_acquire`, use `PoolUtil.release_node` on end, spawn via `gun.gd` `_spawn_from_pool` (or `ScenePool.acquire` elsewhere).
- Add prewarm entry on `ScenePool` if the type spawns frequently.

## Must not

- Do not rename or remove `ObjectPools` without updating `game.gd`, `gun.gd`, `mob.gd`, and grep for `ObjectPools` / `ScenePool`.
- Do not `queue_free()` pooled mobs, exp orbs, or gun-managed projectiles while pooling is enabled (breaks pool invariants).
